{"Title":"Walkthrough","Contents":"\u003Cp>\u003Ca href=\"about.page\">About ObjectCloud\u003C/a>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>This page walks you through basic installation and simple uses of ObjectCloud.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch1>Download and Install\u003C/h1>\n\u003Cp>Download ObjectCloud from \u003Ca target=\"_blank\" title=\"\" href=\"http://andrewrondeau.com/ObjectCloud/Releases/\">http://andrewrondeau.com/ObjectCloud/Releases/\u003C/a> and extract the zip file to wherever\nyou plan on installing ObjectCloud.&nbsp; (Make sure to select the newest file.)&nbsp; ObjectCloud currently does not\ninstall itself and must be started manually.&nbsp; On Mac and Linux,\nObjectCloud requires a recent version of \u003Ca target=\"_blank\" title=\"\" href=\"http://www.go-mono.com/mono-downloads/download.html\">Mono\u003C/a>.&nbsp; (2.4)&nbsp; See the \u003Ca target=\"\" title=\"\" href=\"/Docs/requirements.page\">requirements\u003C/a> for more information.\u003C/p>\u003Cp style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\u003Cspan style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note\u003C/span>:&nbsp; \u003Cspan style=\"font-style: italic;\">Be careful where you extract ObjectCloud.&nbsp; It might not work if extracted onto a network share, or in a folder synchronized by a utility like \u003Ca target=\"_blank\" title=\"\" href=\"http://www.getdropbox.com/\">Dropbox\u003C/a>.\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\n\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch1>Running ObjectCloud\u003C/h1>ObjectCloud is a server that is run at the command-line.&nbsp; There is no GUI except for what is seen in the web browser.\u003Cbr>\n\u003Ch2>Windows\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Open the directory that you installed ObjectCloud into, and double-click on the ObjectCloud application file.&nbsp; (Either ObjectCloud or ObjectCloud.exe)\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2>Mac / Linux\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Open a shell (terminal) and cd to the directory that ObjectCloud is installed into.&nbsp; Type \"mono ObjectCloud.exe\"\u003C/p>\u003Cp style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\u003Cspan style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note\u003C/span>:&nbsp; \u003Cspan style=\"font-style: italic;\">ObjectCloud requires \u003C/span>\u003Ca style=\"font-style: italic;\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"\" href=\"http://www.go-mono.com/mono-downloads/download.html\">mono\u003C/a>\u003Cspan style=\"font-style: italic;\"> on Linux and Mac\u003C/span>.\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch1>Viewing ObjectCloud from a browser for the first time\u003C/h1>\n\u003Cp>ObjectCloud takes a few seconds to load.&nbsp; While it is loading, you will see some gibberish fly through the screen.&nbsp; This is because ObjectCloud uses the \u003Ca target=\"_blank\" title=\"\" href=\"http://www.springframework.net/\">Spring.Net\u003C/a> framework for \u003Ca target=\"_blank\" title=\"\" href=\"http://www.springframework.net/doc-latest/reference/html/objects.html#objects-factory-collaborators\">dependency injection\u003C/a>.\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>When ObjectCloud is ready, you will see a screen like the following:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"walkthrough/server%20started.png\" align=\"none\">\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\u003Cspan style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note\u003C/span>:&nbsp; \u003Cspan style=\"font-style: italic;\">Windows might give you a warning when you run ObjectCloud for the first time.&nbsp; This is expected, and it is because ObjectCloud lets external computers connect to your computer.&nbsp; Instruct windows to let ObjectCloud access the internet.\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>When ObjectCloud is ready for you to view it in a web browser, it says  \"Server is waiting for a new connection at...\"&nbsp; The URL given is where your web browser can access  ObjectCloud.&nbsp; The URL defaults to the host computer's IP at port 1080.&nbsp; Your URL will most likely be different then the one shown above.\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\u003Cspan style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Notes:\u003C/span>&nbsp; \u003Cspan style=\"font-style: italic;\">ObjectCloud needs to know its\nhostname in order for OpenID and messaging to work correctly.&nbsp; It\ndefaults to using its IP as its hostname.&nbsp; ObjectCloud also defaults to port 1080 due to security restrictions in Unixes.&nbsp; This behavior allows you to test-drive ObjectCloud in a secure manner on a local network without extensive configuration.&nbsp; Setting a proper hostname and port are discussed in \u003C/span>\u003Ca style=\"font-style: italic;\" target=\"\" title=\"\" href=\"public_internet.page\">Putting ObjectCloud on the public internet\u003C/a>\u003Cspan style=\"font-style: italic;\">.\u003C/span>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Open a browser using the provided URL:&nbsp; (http://those weird numbers/)&nbsp; Don't forget to use the :1080!\u003C/p>\u003Cp style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\u003Cspan style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Notes:\u003C/span>&nbsp; \u003Cspan style=\"font-style: italic;\">ObjectCloud is primarily tested with Mozilla and Safari on Mac; although some Internet Explorer testing is performed.&nbsp; When using Internet Explorer, turn compatibility mode on.&nbsp; Even though browser compatibility is a high priority; using Internet Explorer is strongly discouraged in this version.\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>If all goes well, you will see a page similar to the following:\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/browser%20opened.png\" align=\"none\">\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Did you get some error when trying to connect?&nbsp; Don't forget to add :1080 to the URL!&nbsp; (It's circled above.)&nbsp; Make sure you type in the URL displayed from the \"Server is waiting for a new connection at...\" message.\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Now that you've connected to ObjectCloud, it's time to log in.&nbsp; For now, log in as root.&nbsp; Type \"root\" into the Username box, and \"root\" into the password box.&nbsp; Click on the \"login\" button.&nbsp; Omit the quotes.\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Ch2>Changing Root's password\u003C/h2>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"Our gorgeously handsome programmer, Andrew Rondeau, expresses his fear about pickpockets and loose women\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/beware-of-pickpockets-and-l.jpg\" align=\"right\">The first thing you should do once you get ObjectCloud running is to change root's password.&nbsp; If you don't do, hackers will fill up your ObjectCloud instance with gremlins, pickpockets, and loose women.&nbsp; They might also blackmail you with pictures from that party in...&nbsp; Oh wait, we agreed never to talk about that again!\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/logged%20in.png\" align=\"none\">\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Click on the \"My Account\" to go to root's account administration page.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/change%20password.png\" align=\"none\">\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Type in the old password. \"root,\" and the new password.&nbsp; (Note, there's a UI glitch; after typing in the new password twice, click anywhere on the page to enable the \"Change Password\" button.)\u003C/p>\u003Cp>You should see a dialog that says, \"Password Changed\"\u003C/p>\u003Ch1>Create a Page\u003C/h1>\u003Cp>After changing root's password, click on the \"My Files\" link to access root's files.\u003C/p>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/my%20files.png\" align=\"none\">\u003Cbr>\u003Cp>After clicking on \"My Files,\" you will see root's directory.&nbsp; It should be empty.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/empty%20home%20directory.png\" align=\"none\">\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Click on the \"create\" button to create a new file.&nbsp; You will see a \"new file.page created\" dialog.\u003C/p>\u003Ch2>Edit the Page\u003Cbr>\u003C/h2>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/edit%20file.png\" align=\"none\">\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Click on the context button next to \"new file.page\".&nbsp; Select \"Edit.\"&nbsp; nicEdit, a simple browser-based page editor, will open in either a new window or tab depending on how your browser is configured.&nbsp; (\u003Cspan style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note:\u003C/span>&nbsp; The \u003Cspan style=\"font-style: italic;\">nicEdit page is a little wonky on Internet Explorer\u003C/span>.)\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/editor.png\" align=\"none\">\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Enter a title, type in some text, and then click on the disk icon to save.&nbsp; You will see a dialog with the \"Saved\" message.&nbsp; NicEdit is based on code downloaded from \u003Ca target=\"_blank\" title=\"http://nicedit.com/\" href=\"http://nicedit.com/\">http://nicedit.com/\u003C/a>.\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Ch2>Include an Image\u003C/h2>\u003Cp>ObjectCloud includes some functionality for including images in .page files.\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Ch3>Upload an Image\u003C/h3>\u003Cp>To upload an image go back to the root user's folder.&nbsp; Scroll down to \"Upload\" and click \"Browse.\"&nbsp; Find the image to upload, and click \"Upload.\"\u003C/p>\u003Cp style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\u003Cspan style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note\u003C/span>:&nbsp; \u003Cspan style=\"font-style: italic;\">When uploading with internet explorer, you will need to rename the file after uploading.\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/upload%20image.png\" align=\"none\">\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Ch3>Create and Edit an Image (experimental)\u003C/h3>\u003Cp>To create a blank image, create a new file and select one of the image types.\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>You can  edit an image by selecting the drop-down menu and choosing \"Edit.\"\u003C/p>\u003Cp style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\u003Cspan style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note\u003C/span>:&nbsp; \u003Cspan style=\"font-style: italic;\">In-browser image editing is experimental.&nbsp; Internet Explorer is not supported.\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Ch3>Include an Image\u003Cbr>\u003C/h3>\u003Cp>To include an image, return to nicEdit.&nbsp; Click on the image icon.&nbsp; Delete the \"http://\" and enter the full path to the image.\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/include%20image.png\" align=\"none\">\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Ch2>View the created page\u003Cbr>\u003C/h2>\u003Cp>Go back to the root user's directory.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/view%20new%20page.png\" align=\"none\">\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Click on \"new file.page\".&nbsp; The document that you just created will open in a new window or tab.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/document%20created.png\" align=\"none\">\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Ch1>Create an Account\u003C/h1>\u003Cp>Open the \"Create Account\" link in a new page or tab.&nbsp; (We will come back to this page when we share files.)\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/create%20user.png\" align=\"none\">\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Type in the new user's user name and password, then click \"Create Account.\"\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/create%20account.png\" align=\"none\">\u003Cbr>\u003Cp>When you click \"create account,\" you will see a dialog stating that the new user was created and you be logged in as the new user.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/account%20created.png\" align=\"none\">\u003C/p>\u003Cp style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\u003Cspan style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note:\u003C/span>&nbsp; \u003Cspan style=\"font-style: italic;\">By default, members of the general public can not create accounts on ObjectCloud.&nbsp; Only the root user and members of the administrators group can create accounts.&nbsp; This is to protect an ObjectCloud instance from being overrun by gremlins, hobgoblins, and loose women.&nbsp; By default, anyone can log in with an OpenID.\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Ch1>Share the page with the new Account\u003C/h1>\u003Cp>Go back to the window or tab with the page you created as the root user.&nbsp; (Don't forget that you're logged in as the account you just created above!)&nbsp; Click refresh.&nbsp; You should see a permission denied error.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/permission%20denied.png\" align=\"none\">\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Login as root, and then go back to the window or tab with the root user's directory.&nbsp; Click on the context menu button next to \"new file.page.\"&nbsp; (\u003Cspan style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note:\u003C/span>&nbsp; \u003Cspan style=\"font-style: italic;\">Internet Explorer users must right-click in this version.\u003C/span>)&nbsp; Select \"Permissions.\"\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/open%20permissions.png\" align=\"none\">\u003C/p>\u003Cp>The permissions editor should open in a new window or tab.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/add%20permission.png\" align=\"none\">\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Type in the user name and click \"add\".\u003C/p>\u003Cp style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\u003Cspan style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note:\u003C/span>&nbsp; \u003Cspan style=\"font-style: italic;\">You can grant permissions to an OpenID.&nbsp; This allows anyone to view a file without having an account on this instance of ObjectCloud.\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>When you click \"add,\" you will see a dialog with \"Permission Set to Read\" and the newly added permission will show in the GUI.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/permission%20added.png\" align=\"none\">\u003C/p>\u003Cp>Go back to the tab or window that's viewing \"new file.page.\"&nbsp; Click the \"logout\" button, then log in as the new user.&nbsp; You should see the file.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/shared%20with%20gwbasic.png\" align=\"none\">\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>You can also share the file with people who aren't logged in by sharing with \"everybody.\"&nbsp; You will need to re-log in as root before you can modify the permissions on \"new file.page.\"\u003Cbr>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/add%20permission%20for%20everybody.png\" align=\"none\">\u003C/p>\u003Cp>\u003Cimg alt=\"\" src=\"/Docs/walkthrough/shared%20with%20everybody.png\" align=\"none\">\u003C/p>\u003Ch1>Stopping ObjectCloud\u003C/h1>\n\u003Cp>On Windows, ObjectCloud stops when a key is pushed.&nbsp; On Linux or\nMac, ObjectCloud stops when it gets a SIGINT signal after you push\ncontrol-C.\u003Cbr>\n\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Ca href=\"about.page\">About ObjectCloud\u003C/a>\u003C/p>\n"}